news.title: Ahmedabad's wetlands disappearing at alarming rate
news.para: The city’s lakes have been degrading and disappearing at an alarming rate, according to a new study by researchers at Gujarat University’s department of botany, bioinformatics and climate change impacts management.

news.title: Silkyara: Construction waste dumps a call to disaster
news.para: For half a decade now, villagers of Manjh Gaon and Vaana Gaon have been living under the looming threat of toxicwaste.

news.title: Chandigarh: Protest against eviction notices to 63 houses
news.para: ​The residents of the colony joined the protest. Unit president H S Lucky emphasised the historic role of the Congress Party in upliftment of the weaker sections of the society through comprehensive housing schemes.

news.title: Gurugram: No nod yet, work on Dwarka expressway service roads may begin only in Jan
news.para: Officials said the approval and allotment process is likely to be completed soon and the construction work will begin by January.

news.title: Patna HC asks EOU to expedite probe against Agrani group of companies
news.para: ​These cases were lodged by the flat buyers, who have allegedly been duped by this company. The real estate firm has allegedly embezzled Rs100 crore of the buyers that was taken in the name of booking flats.

news.title: Colive taps venture capital funds in bid to raise $20 million
news.para: The company has plans to increase its room capacity by twofold in Mumbai, Pune, Bengaluru, Hyderabad and Chennai.

news.title: Razing of building won't hurt tenancy rights: Bombay high court
news.para: The HC vacation bench of Justices Sharmila Deshmukh and S V Marne, on request of the petitioners' lawyer for time to vacate their commercial premises, gave them till December 31 to move out.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels India seeks administration help to vacate unsafe towers at Paradiso
news.para: Chintels India on Monday wrote to deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav seeking the district administration’s support and security arrangements to vacate buildings and barricade unsafe common areas.

news.title: Kesoram Industries weighs debt management options
news.para: Kesoram, in a stock exchange filing, announced that its scheduled board meeting on Thursday will also address the potential withdrawal of the proposed demerger of its wholly-owned subsidiary, Cygnet Industries.

news.title: MREAT tweaks RERA's order, Neelkamal Realtors' promoter to pay for flat delay
news.para: The tribunal stated that the housing regulator’s order “suffered from infirmities”, and it has also directed the promoter of the housing project, Neelkamal Realtors, to execute an agreement for sale and hand over possession of the flat at an early date on receiving the occupancy certificate.

news.title: BDR Pharma CMD's family buys apartments in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 81 crore
news.para: The performance in terms of stamp duty collection led by the heightened activity in premium and mid-income housing segments have also pushed the state exchequer’s revenue higher for several months.

news.title: China approves first batch of consumption-related REITs
news.para: The commercial real estate investment trusts (REITs) approved by the China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) are backed by properties owned by SCPG Holdings Co. Ltd., Shanghai Xingxiumao Business Management Co. Ltd, and the commercial unit of China Resources Land.

news.title: Signa set to make further insolvency filings: Sources
news.para: Signa, controlled by an Austrian magnate but whose business is anchored in Germany, held talks with Elliott Investment Management to try to raise funds, according to one of the people, describing the company's scramble for cash.

news.title: Odisha RERA scraps land deal for violating registration norms
news.para: Sources said the landowner had created around 20 sub-plots of about an acre of land in Balianta area on the city outskirts without registering the bigger plot with ORERA and was selling them to multiple buyers.

news.title: With eye on sustainability, Goa government embarks on 3D-based urban planning
news.para: The agency has invited an expression of interest from interested firms for setting up procurement, implementation, and support of a 3D application for urban planning.

news.title: Nashik civic body to map properties using GIS
news.para: At present, the city has over 5.2 lakh properties on record with the property tax department. Moreover, properties that are still not on record will also be identified due to GIS mapping.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body fines 40% checked construction sites for air pollution
news.para: The facts came to the fore after checks by 32 dedicated squads formed by the Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) in 16 wards to take action in this regard.

news.title: Chennai: No green nod for resorts, villas in Mudaliarkuppam
news.para: Residents of Thazuthalaikuppam, a village in the neighbourhood, had filed a case seeking directions from the tribunal to demolish all 'illegal' constructions in Paramankeni and Mudaliarkuppam villages.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh sets up panel to study stone crusher units
news.para: The multi-sector committee, in its interim report submitted to the government, has submitted that along with the climatic change, the unscientific and illegal mining along the river beds was responsible for the natural calamity in the state that caused huge damage to life and property.

news.title: No metro link, Greater Noida West homebuyers hit the streets
news.para: The protest follows the PMO’s rejection of the detailed project report (DPR), along with the proposed skywalk linking DMRC’s Sector 51 metro station with Noida NMRC’s Sector 52 metro station. A fresh DPR will be made now.
